[1] WHO: Ebola response roadmap - situation report
Date: Wed 24 Dec 2014
Source: WHO [edited]
http://apps.who.int/ebolaweb/sitreps/20141224/20141224.pdf


Ebola response roadmap - situation report 24 Dec 2014
-----------------------------------------------------
Summary
-------
A total of 19 497 confirmed, probable, and suspected cases of Ebola virus disease (EVD) have been reported in 4 affected countries (Guinea, Liberia, Mali and Sierra Leone) and 4 previously affected countries (Nigeria, Senegal, Spain and the United States of America) in the 7 days to 21 Dec 2014 (week 51) [sic]*. There have been 7588 reported deaths (case definitions are provided in Annex 1).

[*They do not mean in 7 days; these are the totals since the start of data collection in March 2014 -- see below. However, they show 928 more cases and 688 more deaths than the 18 569 confirmed, probable, and suspected cases of EVD and 6900 deaths reported a week ago in the WHO sitrep of 17 Dec 2014, or well over 100 new cases and almost 100 deaths a day http://who.int/csr/disease/ebola/situation-reports/en. - Mod.JW]

Reported case incidence is fluctuating in Guinea and declining in Liberia. In Sierra Leone, there are signs that the increase in incidence has slowed, and that incidence may no longer be increasing. The country's west is now experiencing the most intense transmission in the affected countries, and response efforts have been strengthened to curb the spread of disease in the area. The reported case fatality rate in the 3 intense transmission countries among all cases for whom a definitive outcome is known is 70 per cent...

Countries with widespread and intense transmission
--------------------------------------------------
A total of 19 463 confirmed, probable, and suspected cases of EVD and 7573 deaths have been reported up to the end of 21 Dec 2014 by the Ministries of Health of Guinea and Sierra Leone, and 20 Dec 2014 by the Ministry of Health of Liberia (table 1). The data are reported through WHO country offices...

--
communicated by:
