[6] Suspected, monitored, quarantined, prevention

Sierra Leone: declares Ebola lockdown in north
----------------------------------------------
Date: Tue 23 Dec 2014
Source: Daily Mail, AFP report [edited]
http://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/afp/article-2886548/Sierra-Leone-declares-five-day-Ebola-lockdown-north.html


The Sierra Leone government on Wednesday [24 Dec 2014] declared a 5-day lockdown in the country's north to step up efforts to contain the Ebola epidemic, while making an exception for Christmas. "Muslims and Christians are not allowed to hold services in mosques and churches throughout the lockdown except for Christians on Christmas Day (Thu 25 Dec 2014)," Alie Kamara, resident minister for the Northern Region, told AFP. The lockdown is designed "to intensify the containment of the Ebola virus," he said, adding: "We are working to break the chain of transmission." Deputy communication minister Theo Nicol said "The lockdown for 5 days ... is meant for us to get an accurate picture of the situation," adding: "Other districts will carry on with their own individual lockdown after this if they deemed it necessary."...

